The paper deals with an online matching problem, which is a classic topic in computer science. The use of metric spaces and the aspect ratio parameter suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) categories. The use of a randomized algorithm and the analysis of its competitive ratio suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. Finally, the suggestion that the MPMD problem is part of a general framework of online problems with delayed service suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category.
